
[1]sacredness

   SA'CREDNESS, n.

   1. The state of being sacred, or consecrated to God, to his worship or
   to religious uses; holiness; sanctity; as the sacredness of the
   sanctuary or its worship; the sacredness of the sabbath; the sacredness
   of the clerical office.

   2. Inviolableness; as the sacredness of marriage vows or of a trust.
